item.title: The system cannot find the path specified
item.dc:creator: @kingofnone kingofnone
item.description:
@kingofnone wrote:

DUDE STOP POSTIN ON THIS WE HAVE TRIED TO HELP YOU!

i will try one more time…

apparently you dont have your jdk set in the compiler right…
what you do is

go to your compiler
right click it and click edit
then there will be something along the lines of

set pro=%programfiles%\Java\jdk1.6.0_03 set pro2=%programfiles%\Java\jdk1.6.0_03
now change the jdk to your jdk…
mine that i use is jdk6u3(which means jdk1.6.0_03 change yours to your jdk!! if you have jdk6u5 then change to jdk1.6.0_05
if you have jdk6u6 do
jdk1.6.0_06
you get the point!!!
